## Context

- Completed Phase 2 tasks (104-106) for innate immunity deficiency model
- All used group-level proxy analysis (PANS vs controls) since per-patient WES genotypes unavailable
- Pipeline code in: src/pandas_pans/innate_immunity_deficiency_model/
- Outputs in: output/pandas_pans/innate-immunity-deficiency-model/ (20 CSV files total)

## Key findings

- Task 104: Lectin complement FCN1 trends higher in PANS (bulk FC=1.40, scRNA neutrophils FC=1.89); MBL2/MASP near-zero in PBMCs (liver-expressed)
- Task 105: ISGs consistently elevated in PANS (OAS1 FC=1.64, ISG15 FC=1.58) — consistent with cGAS-STING activation from TREX1/SAMHD1 variants
- Task 106: Expression-based composite deficiency score does NOT separate PANS from controls (p>0.3) — innate deficiency is functional/genetic, not transcriptomic
- This is a significant insight: loss-of-function variants impair protein activity without reducing mRNA levels

## Data limitations
- Per-patient WES data (Vettiatil 2026) still not available — human task 149 pending
- Small sample sizes (n=5 PANS, n=4 controls scRNA; n=9 pre, n=10 control bulk) limit statistical power
- Expression data (Han VX) and variant data (Vettiatil 2026) are from different cohorts

## Next tasks
- Tasks 107-110 remain pending (model testing, mechanistic modeling)
- Task 107 (deficiency score vs clinical outcomes) needs clinical outcome metadata
- Task 108 (PANDAS vs PANS innate profiles) needs subtype labels in expression data
- Tasks 109-110 (network model, autoantibody prediction) are Phase 4
- All Phase 3-4 tasks depend on additional data not yet in the repository
